Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State on Thursday approved the appointment of 24 new Special Advisers (SAs) and Senior Special Assistants (SSAs). Mr Tijjani Ahmed, Secretary to the State Government (SSG) in a statement to NAN, said the appointment was with immediate effect, adding that a date would be announce for their inauguration. Ahmed said that the appointees include 12 Special Assistant, 12 Senior Special Assistants. He said the SAs are – Mr Aliyu Tasha; Mr Hashimu Gurku; Mr Mohammed Yakubu; Mr Yankubu Kwanta; Mr Hudu Tafida; Mr Sanusi Giza; Mr David Ayele; Ms Munirat Abdullahi and Ms Hajurat Danyaro among others. Ahmed named some of the SSAs to include – Ms Fatima Ahmed, Mr Idris Mohammed, Mr Haruna Idris, Mr Yusuf Mada, Mr Imran Jibrin and Ms Josephine Mark. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.